<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0021/44b.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Minister of Colombia</gloss>.</hi><note n="3" xml:id="d3fn3">Mutatis mutandis, to the diplomatic representatives
                                at Washington of the other Governments concerned.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For your information, I have the honor to
                            enclose a copy of an instruction which has this day been sent to the
                            American Minister at Bogotá in relation to the termination under the Act
                            of Congress of March 4, last, of certain treaty articles concerning the
                            arrest and imprisonment of officers and seamen deserting, or charged
                            with desertion, from the merchant vessels of either country within the
                            jurisdiction of the other.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>